Teabot:  The image shows an illustration of a wizard-like figure holding a gun, with text that reads "I might be out of spells but I'm not out of shells." This is a humorous meme that plays on the stereotype of wizards and magic users being ineffectual when it comes to physical combat. The joke implies that while the wizard may have used up all their magical abilities, they still have bullets left for shooting things like shells, which are not living creatures but rather protective coverings for important documents or electronic equipment. It's a play on the idea that magic users often rely on magic in combat situations and would be at a loss when faced with physical threats without it, but the wizard here is still prepared for the situation with another means of defense (in this case, bullets).
